WEBVTT

00:00:00.620 --> 00:00:04.620
Welcome to JW Broadcasting.

00:00:04.620 --> 00:00:09.619
In this month's program, we'll see how much the Bible can improve our lives,

00:00:09.619 --> 00:00:13.619
how it can save us from lasting harm,

00:00:13.619 --> 00:00:16.620
how it can help us to get along with one another,

00:00:16.620 --> 00:00:21.620
and how it reassures us that even if we stumble,

00:00:21.620 --> 00:00:24.620
Jehovah will help us find our way back.

00:00:24.620 --> 00:00:27.620
From the life of John the Baptist,

00:00:27.620 --> 00:00:30.620
we'll learn how to cope with fear,

00:00:30.620 --> 00:00:32.619
rejoice when others are blessed,

00:00:32.619 --> 00:00:38.619
and maintain a positive attitude even when facing problems.

00:00:38.619 --> 00:00:41.619
We'll see from Brother Gordon McKay's experience

00:00:41.619 --> 00:00:45.619
that Jehovah wants us to draw close to him,

00:00:45.619 --> 00:00:49.619
even if we've had a serious spiritual setback.

00:00:49.619 --> 00:00:54.619
And our newest music video extends a warm invitation to all

00:00:54.619 --> 00:00:57.619
who find themselves estranged from Jehovah

00:00:57.619 --> 00:01:00.619
and his imperfect but faithful family.

00:01:00.619 --> 00:01:07.620
It reminds us of what a wonderful blessing our spiritual home is.

00:01:07.620 --> 00:01:13.620
This is the February 2024 edition of JW Broadcasting.

00:01:13.620 --> 00:01:35.609
When I was young, one of my favorite desserts

00:01:35.609 --> 00:01:38.609
was my mother's sweet potato pie.

00:01:38.609 --> 00:01:40.609
It always tasted the same.

00:01:40.609 --> 00:01:45.609
To me, it was perfect every time.

00:01:45.609 --> 00:01:47.609
I'd often ask her,

00:01:47.609 --> 00:01:52.609
what do you put in here to make it taste so good?

00:01:52.609 --> 00:01:54.609
She'd always respond,

00:01:54.609 --> 00:01:58.609
I just use the same stuff every time.

00:01:58.609 --> 00:02:01.609
In other words, number one, she wasn't going to tell me,

00:02:01.609 --> 00:02:05.609
and two, she had a recipe that worked,

00:02:05.609 --> 00:02:08.610
so she never changed it.

00:02:08.610 --> 00:02:12.610
Well, the Bible is like a cookbook,

00:02:12.610 --> 00:02:14.610
full of recipes that work,

00:02:14.610 --> 00:02:19.610
that can make our life spiritually successful.

00:02:19.610 --> 00:02:24.610
Please note how Paul explains the benefits of these recipes

00:02:24.610 --> 00:02:29.610
at 2 Timothy, chapter 3, verses 16 and 17.

00:02:29.610 --> 00:02:32.610
All scripture is inspired of God

00:02:32.610 --> 00:02:34.610
and beneficial for teaching,

00:02:34.610 --> 00:02:37.610
for reproving, for setting things straight,

00:02:37.610 --> 00:02:40.610
for disciplining and righteousness,

00:02:40.610 --> 00:02:43.610
so that the man of God may be fully competent,

00:02:43.610 --> 00:02:48.610
completely equipped for every good work.

00:02:48.610 --> 00:02:52.610
Sometimes the recipe from God's inspired word

00:02:52.610 --> 00:02:56.610
comes in a form of a Bible example.

00:02:56.610 --> 00:02:58.610
As we study that example,

00:02:58.610 --> 00:03:03.610
we extract qualities and attitudes that we can imitate.

00:03:03.610 --> 00:03:08.610
Other times, there's a list of qualities,

00:03:08.610 --> 00:03:11.610
such as the various aspects of the fruitage of God's spirit,

00:03:11.610 --> 00:03:14.610
mentioned in Galatians chapter 5,

00:03:14.610 --> 00:03:16.610
or the list of positive things to consider

00:03:16.610 --> 00:03:19.610
at Philippians 4, 8, and 9.

00:03:19.610 --> 00:03:23.610
And of course, there are numerous Bible principles

00:03:23.610 --> 00:03:28.610
that we can use to help us make good decisions.

00:03:28.610 --> 00:03:32.610
Meditating on and applying these principles,

00:03:32.610 --> 00:03:36.610
qualities, and examples can be a recipe

00:03:36.610 --> 00:03:40.610
that contributes to spiritual success.

00:03:40.610 --> 00:03:42.610
Let's consider one example.

00:03:42.610 --> 00:03:47.610
It's recorded in 1 Peter 3 and verse 8.

00:03:47.610 --> 00:03:51.610
Take note of the ingredients.

00:03:51.610 --> 00:03:54.610
All of you have unity of mind,

00:03:54.610 --> 00:03:58.610
fellow feeling, brotherly affection,

00:03:58.610 --> 00:04:02.610
tender compassion, and humility.

00:04:02.610 --> 00:04:07.610
This is a recipe of five beautiful qualities

00:04:07.610 --> 00:04:10.610
that contribute to our spiritual success.

00:04:10.610 --> 00:04:12.610
How so?

00:04:12.610 --> 00:04:14.610
Let's discuss the ingredients.

00:04:14.610 --> 00:04:19.610
Peter first mentions unity of mind.

00:04:19.610 --> 00:04:21.610
The footnote says,

00:04:21.610 --> 00:04:24.610
think in agreement.

00:04:24.610 --> 00:04:28.610
So we must think in agreement with one another,

00:04:28.610 --> 00:04:32.610
but especially with Jehovah and his organization.

00:04:32.610 --> 00:04:34.610
In what way?

00:04:34.610 --> 00:04:38.610
The latter part of Isaiah 35 says,

00:04:38.610 --> 00:04:43.610
your strength will be in keeping calm and showing trust.

00:04:43.610 --> 00:04:47.610
That's exactly what the faithful slave has done.

00:04:47.610 --> 00:04:51.610
So let us have unity of mind with them

00:04:51.610 --> 00:04:56.610
and have the same calmness and confidence in Jehovah

00:04:56.610 --> 00:04:59.610
as we face personal challenges in our life.

00:04:59.610 --> 00:05:03.860
In 2 Kings chapter 4,

00:05:03.860 --> 00:05:06.860
a shoot of my woman is mentioned

00:05:06.860 --> 00:05:10.860
who had confidence in the prophet Elisha.

00:05:10.860 --> 00:05:13.860
She suffered a terrible tragedy in her life.

00:05:13.860 --> 00:05:16.860
Yet she remained calm

00:05:16.860 --> 00:05:20.860
and showed trust in the man of the true God Elisha.

00:05:20.860 --> 00:05:24.860
Her example of trust in Jehovah's representative

00:05:24.860 --> 00:05:26.860
is worthy of invitation.

00:05:26.860 --> 00:05:31.860
In fact, there is an expression she uses in chapter 4

00:05:31.860 --> 00:05:35.860
that conveys the level of trust we want to have in Jehovah

00:05:35.860 --> 00:05:39.860
and his earthly representatives today.

00:05:39.860 --> 00:05:42.860
Let me tell you about this woman.

00:05:42.860 --> 00:05:45.860
She and her husband lived in Shunum.

00:05:45.860 --> 00:05:49.860
Elisha would regularly make encouraging visits with them

00:05:49.860 --> 00:05:52.860
when he was in that city.

00:05:52.860 --> 00:05:55.860
Elisha appreciated their hospitality

00:05:55.860 --> 00:05:58.860
and wanted to do something kind for them.

00:05:58.860 --> 00:06:00.860
What would he do?

00:06:00.860 --> 00:06:05.860
Well, verses 14 through 16 of 2 Kings chapter 4

00:06:05.860 --> 00:06:08.860
indicate that she did not have a son

00:06:08.860 --> 00:06:11.860
and her husband was old.

00:06:11.860 --> 00:06:13.860
So Elisha told her that the next year

00:06:13.860 --> 00:06:16.860
she would be embracing a son.

00:06:16.860 --> 00:06:19.860
Well, as Elisha foretold,

00:06:19.860 --> 00:06:23.860
she gave birth the next year.

00:06:23.860 --> 00:06:28.860
But unfortunately, something drastic happened.

00:06:28.860 --> 00:06:33.860
The child grew up and one day went out to work with his father.

00:06:33.860 --> 00:06:37.860
In verse 19, the boy complained of a headache

00:06:37.860 --> 00:06:41.860
which led to his eventual death.

00:06:41.860 --> 00:06:43.860
Oh my!

00:06:43.860 --> 00:06:45.860
What would this woman do?

00:06:45.860 --> 00:06:48.860
This was her only son.

00:06:48.860 --> 00:06:53.860
Well, she had confidence in the man of the true God Elisha.

00:06:53.860 --> 00:06:57.860
So, she says to her husband in verse 22,

00:06:57.860 --> 00:07:01.860
send me, please, one of the attendants and one of the donkeys

00:07:01.860 --> 00:07:06.860
and let me go quickly to the man of the true God and return.

00:07:06.860 --> 00:07:09.860
In verse 23, her husband asks,

00:07:09.860 --> 00:07:13.860
why are you going to see him today?

00:07:13.860 --> 00:07:17.860
In other words, what can he do for us?

00:07:17.860 --> 00:07:24.860
Note her response at the end of verse 23 and verse 24.

00:07:24.860 --> 00:07:26.860
However, she said,

00:07:26.860 --> 00:07:30.860
everything is all right.

00:07:30.860 --> 00:07:34.860
So she saddled the donkey and said to her attendant,

00:07:34.860 --> 00:07:35.860
go quickly.

00:07:35.860 --> 00:07:38.860
Do not slow down for me unless I tell you to.

00:07:38.860 --> 00:07:42.860
So this calm, trusting woman

00:07:42.860 --> 00:07:47.860
rides about 19 miles or 30 kilometers

00:07:47.860 --> 00:07:52.860
and finds Elisha and he ends up resurrecting her son.

00:07:52.860 --> 00:07:57.860
Her trusting relationship and association with Elisha

00:07:57.860 --> 00:08:00.860
had given her confidence.

00:08:00.860 --> 00:08:02.860
Although she experienced a tragedy,

00:08:02.860 --> 00:08:07.860
she knew that everything was all right.

00:08:07.860 --> 00:08:10.860
Elisha's faith and confidence in Jehovah

00:08:10.860 --> 00:08:14.860
helped this devoted woman also to remain calm

00:08:14.860 --> 00:08:18.860
and confident when facing adversity.

00:08:18.860 --> 00:08:21.860
At Isaiah 41-10,

00:08:21.860 --> 00:08:24.860
note Jehovah's assurance,

00:08:24.860 --> 00:08:28.860
do not be afraid for I am with you.

00:08:28.860 --> 00:08:31.860
Do not be anxious for I am your God.

00:08:31.860 --> 00:08:34.860
I will fortify you.

00:08:34.860 --> 00:08:37.860
Yes, I will help you.

00:08:37.860 --> 00:08:40.860
I will really hold on to you

00:08:40.860 --> 00:08:43.860
with my right hand of righteousness.

00:08:43.860 --> 00:08:46.860
So let's work hard to have unity of mind

00:08:46.860 --> 00:08:49.860
with Jehovah's organization

00:08:49.860 --> 00:08:53.860
by keeping calm and showing trust in Jehovah

00:08:53.860 --> 00:08:56.860
and being confident that with Jehovah's help

00:08:56.860 --> 00:09:00.860
everything will be all right.

00:09:00.860 --> 00:09:03.860
That's a beautiful ingredient

00:09:03.860 --> 00:09:06.860
in this recipe for spiritual success.

00:09:06.860 --> 00:09:10.460
At 1 Peter 3.8,

00:09:10.460 --> 00:09:14.460
Peter next mentions three more ingredients.

00:09:14.460 --> 00:09:17.460
They are aspects of love,

00:09:17.460 --> 00:09:19.460
fellow feeling,

00:09:19.460 --> 00:09:23.460
brotherly affection, tender compassion.

00:09:23.460 --> 00:09:28.460
These aspects of love convey empathy.

00:09:28.460 --> 00:09:31.460
Empathy is the ability to understand

00:09:31.460 --> 00:09:35.460
and share the feelings of another.

00:09:35.460 --> 00:09:38.460
As this system draws to a close,

00:09:38.460 --> 00:09:43.460
Satan will try to divide us from within.

00:09:43.460 --> 00:09:46.460
So love for our brothers and sisters

00:09:46.460 --> 00:09:49.460
and empathizing with one another

00:09:49.460 --> 00:09:51.460
will become ever more important.

00:09:51.460 --> 00:09:55.460
It will serve to unify us.

00:09:55.460 --> 00:10:00.460
Think of the empathy of Jehovah's organization.

00:10:00.460 --> 00:10:03.460
We all have personal challenges,

00:10:03.460 --> 00:10:05.460
but so do our overseers,

00:10:05.460 --> 00:10:09.460
those taking the lead in the organization here on Earth.

00:10:09.460 --> 00:10:12.460
Some of them have lost loved ones in death,

00:10:12.460 --> 00:10:14.460
just like us.

00:10:14.460 --> 00:10:17.460
Some have experienced sickness and anxiety,

00:10:17.460 --> 00:10:19.460
just like us.

00:10:19.460 --> 00:10:23.460
We love them for their empathy.

00:10:23.460 --> 00:10:27.460
Think about the heavenly part of Jehovah's organization.

00:10:27.460 --> 00:10:29.460
Since Satan's rebellion,

00:10:29.460 --> 00:10:31.460
Jehovah has been disappointed,

00:10:31.460 --> 00:10:34.460
saddened, angered,

00:10:34.460 --> 00:10:36.460
at the actions of imperfect men.

00:10:36.460 --> 00:10:38.460
These are real feelings

00:10:38.460 --> 00:10:42.460
that our empathetic Heavenly Father possesses.

00:10:42.460 --> 00:10:47.460
Jesus experienced similar disappointment and sadness

00:10:47.460 --> 00:10:51.460
as he also saw the rebellion of Satan,

00:10:51.460 --> 00:10:54.460
Adam, and Eve and what's resulted.

00:10:54.460 --> 00:10:59.460
In fact, Jesus' understanding became deeper.

00:10:59.460 --> 00:11:04.460
When he became human and began to experience human emotions,

00:11:04.460 --> 00:11:09.460
the April 15, 2002 Watchtower article entitled,

00:11:09.460 --> 00:11:13.460
Empathy, Key to Kindness, and Compassion.

00:11:13.460 --> 00:11:17.460
Mention three ways we can sharpen our sensitivity

00:11:17.460 --> 00:11:20.460
to the knees and feelings of others.

00:11:20.460 --> 00:11:22.460
The first.

00:11:22.460 --> 00:11:24.460
Listen.

00:11:24.460 --> 00:11:26.460
By listening carefully,

00:11:26.460 --> 00:11:30.460
we learn what problems others face.

00:11:30.460 --> 00:11:32.460
And the better we listen,

00:11:32.460 --> 00:11:35.460
the more likely they will open up their hearts

00:11:35.460 --> 00:11:38.460
and reveal their feelings.

00:11:38.460 --> 00:11:41.460
Second, observe.

00:11:41.460 --> 00:11:45.460
Not everyone will openly tell us how they feel

00:11:45.460 --> 00:11:48.460
or what they are going through.

00:11:49.460 --> 00:11:52.460
A keen observer will notice

00:11:52.460 --> 00:11:54.460
when a fellow Christian needs encouragement

00:11:54.460 --> 00:11:57.460
or some practical assistance.

00:11:57.460 --> 00:12:01.460
Third, use your imagination.

00:12:01.460 --> 00:12:05.460
The most powerful way to stimulate empathy

00:12:05.460 --> 00:12:07.460
is to ask yourself,

00:12:07.460 --> 00:12:09.460
if I were in this situation,

00:12:09.460 --> 00:12:11.460
how would I feel?

00:12:11.460 --> 00:12:13.460
How would I respond?

00:12:13.460 --> 00:12:16.460
What would I need?

00:12:16.460 --> 00:12:18.460
So, fellow feeling,

00:12:18.460 --> 00:12:21.460
brotherly affection and tender compassion

00:12:21.460 --> 00:12:24.460
are aspects of loving empathy

00:12:24.460 --> 00:12:28.460
and our valuable ingredients to our spiritual success

00:12:28.460 --> 00:12:33.149
and will benefit others.

00:12:33.149 --> 00:12:37.149
The final quality highlighted in First Peter 3.8

00:12:37.149 --> 00:12:39.149
is humility.

00:12:39.149 --> 00:12:42.149
Why do we need humility?

00:12:42.149 --> 00:12:45.149
Because we need to trust.

00:12:45.149 --> 00:12:48.149
Trust in Jehovah and His organization

00:12:48.149 --> 00:12:51.149
requires humility,

00:12:51.149 --> 00:12:55.149
not relying on our own strength or wisdom.

00:12:55.149 --> 00:12:58.149
Humility helps us to cope

00:12:58.149 --> 00:13:01.149
with whatever God permits.

00:13:01.149 --> 00:13:04.149
When we face anxiety and pressure in our life,

00:13:04.149 --> 00:13:08.149
we may yearn for immediate relief.

00:13:08.149 --> 00:13:11.149
But humility helps us to trust

00:13:11.149 --> 00:13:15.149
that Jehovah knows precisely when

00:13:15.149 --> 00:13:18.149
and how to act in our behalf.

00:13:18.149 --> 00:13:22.149
So, we wait patiently.

00:13:22.149 --> 00:13:26.149
Jehovah always responds to our needs

00:13:26.149 --> 00:13:30.149
in His time and in His way.

00:13:30.149 --> 00:13:32.149
Humility helps us to admit

00:13:32.149 --> 00:13:38.149
that Jehovah's thoughts are vastly superior to our own.

00:13:38.149 --> 00:13:42.149
We recognize our limited discernment

00:13:42.149 --> 00:13:45.149
in comparison with Jehovah's

00:13:45.149 --> 00:13:48.149
all-encompassing perception.

00:13:48.149 --> 00:13:51.149
He sees things we do not discern

00:13:51.149 --> 00:13:56.149
and thus we trust that His way of doing things

00:13:56.149 --> 00:13:59.149
is always best.

00:13:59.149 --> 00:14:02.149
So, as the Great Tribulation approaches,

00:14:02.149 --> 00:14:07.149
humbly trust in Jehovah and His organization.

00:14:08.149 --> 00:14:11.149
First Peter, chapter 5,

00:14:11.149 --> 00:14:15.149
and verse number 6 says this,

00:14:15.149 --> 00:14:17.149
humble yourselves, therefore,

00:14:17.149 --> 00:14:20.149
under the mighty hand of God

00:14:20.149 --> 00:14:24.149
so that He may exalt you in due time.

00:14:24.149 --> 00:14:30.149
Brothers, there is no better place to be

00:14:30.149 --> 00:14:35.149
than under the mighty hand of God.

00:14:35.149 --> 00:14:38.149
Humility is a beautiful ingredient

00:14:38.149 --> 00:14:45.360
that helps us to remain there.

00:14:45.360 --> 00:14:48.360
So, what were the ingredients in our recipe

00:14:48.360 --> 00:14:51.360
for spiritual success?

00:14:51.360 --> 00:14:55.360
First was unity of mind.

00:14:55.360 --> 00:14:59.360
Be at unity with Jehovah's organization today

00:14:59.360 --> 00:15:03.360
by keeping calm and showing trust.

00:15:03.360 --> 00:15:05.360
In the words of the Shunamaid woman

00:15:05.360 --> 00:15:07.360
in King's chapter 4,

00:15:07.360 --> 00:15:11.360
when facing adversity always know that with Jehovah,

00:15:11.360 --> 00:15:15.360
everything is all right.

00:15:15.360 --> 00:15:18.360
Second was fellow feeling,

00:15:18.360 --> 00:15:21.360
brotherly affection and tender compassion,

00:15:21.360 --> 00:15:25.360
all aspects of loving empathy.

00:15:25.360 --> 00:15:29.360
Remember, we're all in this together.

00:15:29.360 --> 00:15:32.360
The celestial chariot is empathetic

00:15:32.360 --> 00:15:34.360
toward what we face

00:15:34.360 --> 00:15:37.360
and what we're drawn to our personal

00:15:37.360 --> 00:15:40.360
and organizational needs.

00:15:40.360 --> 00:15:45.360
Finally, try always to include humility

00:15:45.360 --> 00:15:48.360
in your recipe for success.

00:15:48.360 --> 00:15:52.360
Humility requires trust.

00:15:52.360 --> 00:15:56.360
So, trust that Jehovah's way of doing things

00:15:56.360 --> 00:15:59.360
is always best.

00:15:59.360 --> 00:16:03.360
Psalm 119 verse 105 says

00:16:03.360 --> 00:16:06.360
Bible is a lamp to my foot

00:16:06.360 --> 00:16:10.360
and a light for my path.

00:16:10.360 --> 00:16:13.360
So, take time to consider a portion

00:16:13.360 --> 00:16:16.360
of God's word each day.

00:16:16.360 --> 00:16:21.360
As situations, decisions, and challenges arise,

00:16:21.360 --> 00:16:24.360
search for the right recipe,

00:16:24.360 --> 00:16:29.360
Bible example, Christian quality, principal.

00:16:29.360 --> 00:16:31.360
When you do,

00:16:31.360 --> 00:16:34.360
write up the path ahead of you

00:16:34.360 --> 00:16:41.659
and help you to be spiritually successful.

00:16:41.659 --> 00:16:43.659
We've seen that the Bible's recipes

00:16:43.659 --> 00:16:45.659
can make our life spiritually successful

00:16:45.659 --> 00:16:48.659
and help us improve our relationships.

00:16:48.659 --> 00:16:50.659
In the following interview,

00:16:50.659 --> 00:16:54.659
note how applying a recipe of Bible principles

00:16:54.659 --> 00:17:00.659
can also undo the damage caused by poor decisions.

