00:22:33.859 --> 00:22:36.859
I know you'll enjoy our next segment

00:22:36.859 --> 00:22:38.859
on how a publishing innovation

00:22:38.859 --> 00:22:40.859
invented by our brothers years ago

00:22:40.859 --> 00:22:42.859
has accelerated the translation

00:22:42.859 --> 00:22:43.859
of the good news

00:22:43.859 --> 00:22:45.859
leading to the greatest

00:22:45.859 --> 00:22:49.559
witness in history.

00:22:49.559 --> 00:22:51.559
Jehovah's Witnesses

00:22:51.559 --> 00:22:52.559
are known for publishing

00:22:52.559 --> 00:22:54.559
in hundreds of languages.

00:22:54.559 --> 00:22:55.559
With a website

00:22:55.559 --> 00:22:57.559
recognized as the most widely

00:22:57.559 --> 00:22:59.559
translated in the world.

00:22:59.559 --> 00:23:01.559
But have you ever wondered

00:23:01.559 --> 00:23:03.559
how we're able to release

00:23:03.559 --> 00:23:04.559
our literature

00:23:04.559 --> 00:23:05.559
and print it online

00:23:05.559 --> 00:23:07.559
and so many languages at once?

00:23:07.559 --> 00:23:09.559
The answer involves

00:23:09.559 --> 00:23:11.559
a cutting-edge publishing system

00:23:11.559 --> 00:23:13.559
that our brothers developed

00:23:13.559 --> 00:23:15.559
more than 40 years ago,

00:23:15.559 --> 00:23:17.559
a breakthrough in publishing

00:23:17.559 --> 00:23:19.559
called Maps.

00:23:19.559 --> 00:23:22.559
But just what is Maps?

00:23:22.559 --> 00:23:23.559
Let's find out

00:23:23.559 --> 00:23:25.559
and see how this technology

00:23:25.559 --> 00:23:28.559
has helped to unite Jehovah's people

00:23:28.559 --> 00:23:29.559
and has opened the way

00:23:29.559 --> 00:23:30.559
for us to give

00:23:30.559 --> 00:23:43.900
the greatest witness in history.

00:23:43.900 --> 00:23:44.900
God's people

00:23:44.900 --> 00:23:45.900
have long understood

00:23:45.900 --> 00:23:47.900
the need to share the truth

00:23:47.900 --> 00:23:50.900
in as many languages as possible.

00:23:50.900 --> 00:23:53.900
Revelation 14.6

00:23:53.900 --> 00:23:54.900
prophesied

00:23:54.900 --> 00:23:55.900
that the good news

00:23:55.900 --> 00:23:56.900
would be preached

00:23:56.900 --> 00:23:57.900
to every nation

00:23:57.900 --> 00:23:59.900
and tribe and tongue

00:23:59.900 --> 00:24:01.900
and people.

00:24:01.900 --> 00:24:02.900
So as far back

00:24:02.900 --> 00:24:04.900
as the late 1800s,

00:24:04.900 --> 00:24:05.900
the early Bible students

00:24:05.900 --> 00:24:07.900
translated our literature

00:24:07.900 --> 00:24:09.900
into languages other than English

00:24:09.900 --> 00:24:11.900
so that people could learn the truth

00:24:11.900 --> 00:24:13.900
in their mother tongue.

00:24:13.900 --> 00:24:15.900
But for decades,

00:24:15.900 --> 00:24:16.900
publishing the good news

00:24:16.900 --> 00:24:18.900
in many languages

00:24:18.900 --> 00:24:21.900
was a labor-intensive process.

00:24:21.900 --> 00:24:22.900
Imagine yourself

00:24:22.900 --> 00:24:24.900
working at a Bethel-Printry

00:24:24.900 --> 00:24:26.900
decades ago.

00:24:26.900 --> 00:24:27.900
It's hot

00:24:27.900 --> 00:24:29.900
and loud.

00:24:29.900 --> 00:24:30.900
Printing required

00:24:30.900 --> 00:24:32.900
the use of a liner type machine,

00:24:32.900 --> 00:24:34.900
which turned molten lead

00:24:34.900 --> 00:24:36.900
into small metal slabs

00:24:36.900 --> 00:24:37.900
of type,

00:24:37.900 --> 00:24:38.900
called slugs,

00:24:38.900 --> 00:24:41.900
one line at a time.

00:24:41.900 --> 00:24:43.900
Workers had to

00:24:43.900 --> 00:24:45.900
meticulously compose pages

00:24:45.900 --> 00:24:47.900
by arranging the slugs

00:24:47.900 --> 00:24:49.900
into large metal frames

00:24:49.900 --> 00:24:50.900
that were used

00:24:50.900 --> 00:24:52.900
to make special embossed mats.

00:24:52.900 --> 00:24:54.900
Then more hot metal was used

00:24:54.900 --> 00:24:56.900
to cast printing plates

00:24:56.900 --> 00:24:58.900
from the mats.

00:24:58.900 --> 00:25:00.900
And for long press runs,

00:25:00.900 --> 00:25:01.900
the plates then

00:25:01.900 --> 00:25:02.900
had to be electroplated

00:25:02.900 --> 00:25:05.900
with nickel to harden them.

00:25:05.900 --> 00:25:06.900
Finally,

00:25:06.900 --> 00:25:08.900
after removing any irregularities,

00:25:08.900 --> 00:25:09.900
the plates were ready

00:25:09.900 --> 00:25:10.900
to be mounted

00:25:10.900 --> 00:25:13.900
on a large rotary printing press.

00:25:13.900 --> 00:25:15.900
Publishing the same material

00:25:15.900 --> 00:25:17.900
in another language

00:25:17.900 --> 00:25:19.900
meant repeating these pre-press steps

00:25:19.900 --> 00:25:22.900
from beginning to end.

00:25:22.900 --> 00:25:24.900
It took months

00:25:24.900 --> 00:25:26.900
for a single magazine

00:25:26.900 --> 00:25:27.900
to be translated

00:25:27.900 --> 00:25:28.900
from English,

00:25:28.900 --> 00:25:29.900
typeset,

00:25:29.900 --> 00:25:30.900
and printed.

00:25:30.900 --> 00:25:32.900
For books,

00:25:32.900 --> 00:25:34.900
it could take years.

00:25:34.900 --> 00:25:38.140
The days of hot metal

00:25:38.140 --> 00:25:40.140
were quickly ending.

00:25:40.140 --> 00:25:42.140
The printing industry

00:25:42.140 --> 00:25:43.140
began adopting the use

00:25:43.140 --> 00:25:45.140
of photo-type setting

00:25:45.140 --> 00:25:48.140
and offset presses.

00:25:48.140 --> 00:25:49.140
It was time

00:25:49.140 --> 00:25:51.140
to modernize operations

00:25:51.140 --> 00:25:52.140
at Bethel

00:25:52.140 --> 00:25:54.140
and make the transition

00:25:54.140 --> 00:25:56.140
to computers.

00:25:56.140 --> 00:25:57.140
But the brothers faced

00:25:57.140 --> 00:25:59.140
a unique challenge.

00:25:59.140 --> 00:26:01.140
At this point,

00:26:01.140 --> 00:26:03.140
we were already printing literature

00:26:03.140 --> 00:26:06.140
in 167 languages.

00:26:06.140 --> 00:26:08.140
So we needed a solution

00:26:08.140 --> 00:26:10.140
that could handle all those languages

00:26:10.140 --> 00:26:11.140
and more,

00:26:11.140 --> 00:26:12.140
and not one

00:26:12.140 --> 00:26:14.140
of the commercially available systems

00:26:14.140 --> 00:26:18.059
could do that.

00:26:18.059 --> 00:26:20.059
So in 1979,

00:26:20.059 --> 00:26:22.059
a group of brothers and sisters

00:26:22.059 --> 00:26:23.059
were called

00:26:23.059 --> 00:26:24.059
to wash tower farms

00:26:24.059 --> 00:26:27.059
in Wal-Kill, New York.

00:26:27.059 --> 00:26:29.059
To develop a multi-language

00:26:29.059 --> 00:26:31.059
electronic photo-type setting system,

00:26:31.059 --> 00:26:34.059
or MEPs.

00:26:34.059 --> 00:26:36.059
So we got to work

00:26:36.059 --> 00:26:37.059
on building MEPs.

00:26:37.059 --> 00:26:39.059
Some brothers and sisters

00:26:39.059 --> 00:26:40.059
were treated on the hardware,

00:26:40.059 --> 00:26:42.059
the actual circuitry,

00:26:42.059 --> 00:26:43.059
other brothers

00:26:43.059 --> 00:26:44.059
concentrated on the screen itself

00:26:44.059 --> 00:26:46.059
and building that,

00:26:46.059 --> 00:26:47.059
and then others of us

00:26:47.059 --> 00:26:48.059
concentrated on the software,

00:26:48.059 --> 00:26:49.059
the operating system,

00:26:49.059 --> 00:26:51.059
you might say.

00:26:51.059 --> 00:26:52.059
The MEPs team

00:26:52.059 --> 00:26:54.059
designed and built

00:26:54.059 --> 00:26:56.059
almost everything.

00:26:56.059 --> 00:26:57.059
Computers,

00:26:57.059 --> 00:26:58.059
keyboards,

00:26:58.059 --> 00:26:59.059
screens,

00:26:59.059 --> 00:27:00.059
and software.

00:27:00.059 --> 00:27:02.059
They had to.

00:27:02.059 --> 00:27:03.059
Personal computers

00:27:03.059 --> 00:27:04.059
with the power needed

00:27:04.059 --> 00:27:06.059
still weren't available,

00:27:06.059 --> 00:27:07.059
and wouldn't be

00:27:07.059 --> 00:27:10.059
for another few years.

00:27:10.059 --> 00:27:11.059
Another massive part

00:27:11.059 --> 00:27:12.059
of the project involved

00:27:12.059 --> 00:27:14.059
creating the fonts.

00:27:14.059 --> 00:27:15.059
The individual letters

00:27:15.059 --> 00:27:17.059
used to make up the pages

00:27:17.059 --> 00:27:19.059
of text.

00:27:19.059 --> 00:27:20.059
Commercial fonts

00:27:20.059 --> 00:27:22.059
weren't available,

00:27:22.059 --> 00:27:23.059
or were too expensive

00:27:23.059 --> 00:27:26.059
for many of the languages needed.

00:27:26.059 --> 00:27:27.059
So brothers and sisters

00:27:27.059 --> 00:27:30.059
had to draw each character

00:27:30.059 --> 00:27:32.059
by hand,

00:27:32.059 --> 00:27:35.890
and scan them into the computer.

00:27:35.890 --> 00:27:36.890
For some languages,

00:27:36.890 --> 00:27:38.890
this meant drawing

00:27:38.890 --> 00:27:40.890
thousands of characters.

00:27:40.890 --> 00:27:42.890
The software then had to be

00:27:42.890 --> 00:27:44.890
programmed with all the rules

00:27:44.890 --> 00:27:46.890
for spacing and hyphenation,

00:27:46.890 --> 00:27:48.890
so that words and characters

00:27:48.890 --> 00:27:50.890
could be displayed correctly.

00:27:50.890 --> 00:27:52.890
Just three years

00:27:52.890 --> 00:27:54.890
after the project began,

00:27:54.890 --> 00:27:56.890
the first MEPs unit

00:27:56.890 --> 00:27:59.890
was completed in 1982.

00:27:59.890 --> 00:28:01.890
With MEPs,

00:28:01.890 --> 00:28:03.890
an operator could enter text

00:28:03.890 --> 00:28:04.890
at a computer workstation

00:28:04.890 --> 00:28:07.890
in any supported language.

00:28:07.890 --> 00:28:08.890
After this,

00:28:08.890 --> 00:28:09.890
the workstation could be used

00:28:09.890 --> 00:28:10.890
to format the text

00:28:10.890 --> 00:28:13.890
and compose pages.

00:28:13.890 --> 00:28:15.890
This approach

00:28:15.890 --> 00:28:16.890
allowed the brothers

00:28:16.890 --> 00:28:18.890
to use a single-page layout

00:28:18.890 --> 00:28:20.890
to produce the same publication

00:28:20.890 --> 00:28:23.890
for all languages.

00:28:23.890 --> 00:28:25.890
The final pages were then rendered

00:28:25.890 --> 00:28:27.890
on photographic paper,

00:28:27.890 --> 00:28:29.890
transferred to film,

00:28:29.890 --> 00:28:32.890
and used to make printing plates.

00:28:32.890 --> 00:28:34.890
MEPs didn't do the translation

00:28:34.890 --> 00:28:35.890
itself.

00:28:35.890 --> 00:28:36.890
That was,

00:28:36.890 --> 00:28:38.890
and still is,

00:28:38.890 --> 00:28:40.890
a job for human translators.

00:28:40.890 --> 00:28:42.890
But it allowed all the

00:28:42.890 --> 00:28:44.890
pre-press work to be completed

00:28:44.890 --> 00:28:46.890
in a fraction of the time.

00:28:46.890 --> 00:28:48.890
And MEPs achieved

00:28:48.890 --> 00:28:50.890
something even more important

00:28:50.890 --> 00:28:52.890
than increased speed and efficiency.

00:28:52.890 --> 00:28:54.890
It addressed a global

00:28:54.890 --> 00:28:56.890
spiritual need.

00:28:56.890 --> 00:28:58.890
Even before the MEPs

00:28:58.890 --> 00:28:59.890
project began,

00:28:59.890 --> 00:29:00.890
the governing body

00:29:00.890 --> 00:29:01.890
realized

00:29:01.890 --> 00:29:02.890
that if Jehovah's Witnesses

00:29:02.890 --> 00:29:04.890
worldwide could somehow

00:29:04.890 --> 00:29:06.890
study the same material

00:29:06.890 --> 00:29:08.890
each week at meetings,

00:29:08.890 --> 00:29:09.890
it would unite them

00:29:09.890 --> 00:29:11.890
as never before.

00:29:11.890 --> 00:29:12.890
And it was clear

00:29:12.890 --> 00:29:13.890
that with MEPs,

00:29:13.890 --> 00:29:15.890
along with faster presses

00:29:15.890 --> 00:29:16.890
and other adjustments

00:29:16.890 --> 00:29:17.890
in production,

00:29:17.890 --> 00:29:19.890
this could finally

00:29:19.890 --> 00:29:21.890
become a reality.

00:29:21.890 --> 00:29:23.890
In fact, so much time

00:29:23.890 --> 00:29:24.890
to be saved

00:29:24.890 --> 00:29:26.890
in this projected operation,

00:29:26.890 --> 00:29:27.890
that someday

00:29:27.890 --> 00:29:28.890
we might be able

00:29:28.890 --> 00:29:30.890
to bring out the rough path

00:29:30.890 --> 00:29:32.890
in all principal languages,

00:29:32.890 --> 00:29:34.890
with each data issue

00:29:34.890 --> 00:29:35.890
containing

00:29:35.890 --> 00:29:36.890
exactly the same

00:29:36.890 --> 00:29:37.890
spiritual feed

00:29:37.890 --> 00:29:38.890
for the brothers

