Suriname is a heavily forested country in South America

01:00:52.820 --> 01:00:54.820
that's almost like an island.

01:00:54.820 --> 01:00:59.820
It is currently connected by road to any other country.

01:00:59.820 --> 01:01:01.820
On its east and west,

01:01:01.820 --> 01:01:03.820
it's bounded by rivers

01:01:03.820 --> 01:01:06.820
and on the north by the Atlantic Ocean

01:01:06.820 --> 01:01:09.820
and to the south by tropical rainforests,

01:01:09.820 --> 01:01:13.820
savannas, and the mighty Amazon River Basin.

01:01:13.820 --> 01:01:16.820
While Suriname may be one of the smallest countries

01:01:16.820 --> 01:01:18.820
in South America,

01:01:18.820 --> 01:01:23.820
it's abundant wild areas host some of the continent's largest animals.

01:01:23.820 --> 01:01:26.820
The giant ant-eater, for example,

01:01:26.820 --> 01:01:31.820
eats some 35,000 ants in termites a day.

01:01:31.820 --> 01:01:34.820
Also found in Suriname, the taper.

01:01:34.820 --> 01:01:37.820
South America's largest land mammal.

01:01:37.820 --> 01:01:41.820
And the Jaguar, the largest of South American cats.

01:01:41.820 --> 01:01:46.820
Suriname's rich diversity isn't limited to wildlife.

01:01:46.820 --> 01:01:50.820
Its people are one of the most ethnically diverse in the region.

01:01:51.820 --> 01:01:57.820
They're varying customs and foods in rich the country's overall culture.

01:01:57.820 --> 01:02:01.820
In such a heavily forested and diverse country,

01:02:01.820 --> 01:02:08.820
imagine the challenge are over 3,300 brothers face, first reaching

01:02:08.820 --> 01:02:13.820
and then reaching to people in their own languages.

01:02:13.820 --> 01:02:16.820
